The mix command, mx, mixes another edit session with the current session.
An optional block address, or a comma separated pair of addresses,
precedes the command name to tell where to start adding the new audio. A
session number must immediately follow the command name to identify
the session to be added.  If the material being mixed with the current
session needs fading in, or fading out, the time in seconds is given as
one or two numbers, space separated.  For example:

3,9mx2 0.5 2.0

Session #2 is mixed with blocks 3 through nine of the current session,
faded in over 0.5 seconds, and faded out over 2.0 seconds.
